    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen comparing a vim-help/txt file in diff-mode, nvim opens only only the file. No diffmode of the old and new version in the vertical split.\n\n(filetype=help, buftype=)\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```bash\n# fine, split diff view\ngit difftool 62dcd07787 runtime/pack/dist/opt/netrw/autoload/netrw.vim\n\n# opens neovim and shows single help file\ngit difftool 62dcd07787 runtime/pack/dist/opt/netrw/doc/netrw.txt\n\n# check if there are diffs...shows diffs....\ngit diff 62dcd07787 runtime/pack/dist/opt/netrw/doc/netrw.txt\n```\n\n```gitconfig\n# **snipped**\n[difftool]\n    prompt = true\n\n[diff]\n    tool = nvimdiff\n\n[difftool \"nvimdiff\"]\n    cmd = \"nvim -d \\\"$REMOTE\\\" \\\"$LOCAL\\\"\"\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\ndiffmode should also work on help files\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-543+g16d17c50bb\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\n-\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nlinux aarch64\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
